      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Seymour Lavitt, of Rockville, 
CT was an educator in the field of plastics. He taught the fundamentals of plastics from "The Plastics 
Seminars" of Hingham, Massachusetts.</p>
</bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Seymour Lavitt Collection</emph> consists of plastics education material (copies of the "Fundamentals 
of Plastics" resource materials, slides from "Injection Molding" and "Fundamentals" (two lectures given by 
Lavitt), and a film) and professional papers (correspondence about Plastics Fair, 1992-1993 and brochures of Plastics Design/Development 
Associates).</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
